            "body": "Going to monitor this, and if I don't see `TUI already stopped` in the logs may close it.\n\nPotentially helped by https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/35745\n\nThe main source of noise in the CI logs now is https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34016 , which results in lots of:\n\n```\n2025-09-13T20:30:22.7923581Z WRN 2025-09-13T20:12:52.513 ui/c/T1689.14121.0 tui_handle_term_mode:244: TUI: terminal mode 69 detected, state 2\n2025-09-13T20:30:22.7924560Z WRN 2025-09-13T20:12:52.513 ui/c/T1689.14121.0 tui_handle_term_mode:234: TUI: terminal mode 2026 unavailable, state 0\n2025-09-13T20:30:22.7925561Z WRN 2025-09-13T20:12:52.513 ui/c/T1689.14121.0 tui_handle_term_mode:234: TUI: terminal mode 2027 unavailable, state 0\n2025-09-13T20:30:22.7926755Z WRN 2025-09-13T20:12:52.513 ui/c/T1689.14121.0 tui_handle_term_mode:244: TUI: terminal mode 2031 detected, state 2\n2025-09-13T20:30:22.7927793Z WRN 2025-09-13T20:12:52.513 ui/c/T1689.14121.0 tui_handle_term_mode:234: TUI: terminal mode 2048 unavailable, state 0\n```\n\n## TODO\n\nI see that we disable INFO logs here: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/c1648cf820ed379f6abb7cb802680a02a1def755/src/nvim/log.c#L142-L145\n\nNeed to implement runtime log-level selection.",
